comments.body:
@joeyaiello, @jpsnover  : The scenario only repro's if the path for .sys file is provided.
When the path is .sys file, underlying native api 'GetFileAttributes' returns 'INVALID_FILE_ATTRIBUTES' (failure) with error code 32 (ERROR_SHARING_VIOLATION = The process cannot access the file because it is being used by another process.) . 
The solution is to use 'FindFirstFile(path)' in case the error code is 32.  If it does not return INVALID_HANDLE_VALUE (-1) , the file exists.
